e. Two independent clauses cannot be joined by a comma alone. The correct way to join these clauses is to use a comma followed by a coordinating conjunction, such as \"and.\" Choice C corrects this punctuation error by adding the c. Choice C matches the question''s requirement and is consistent with the passage''s central claim or supporting detail. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"D","text":"The study concluded that people who meditate regularly, even for short periods of time, exhibit improved levels of concentration and focus. They also found that meditation can help people to reduce stress and anxiety. The research team further emphasized the importance of finding ways to incorporate meditation into daily life to promote overall well-being.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This choice does not follow from the information given or contains a calculation error. Choice D is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."}]'::jsonb,
